                                <h3>What is NEBOSH INTERNATIONAL GENERAL CERTIFICATE (IGC)?</h3>
                                <br />
                                <p>The NEBOSH International General Certificate in Occupational Health and Safety is one of the globally recognized qualifications offered by NEBOSH. This certification has become almost a mandated certification requirement in Middle East and other part of the world for HSE professionals. A NEBOSH General Certificate is widely accepted as meeting the knowledge requirement for HSE professionals due to its Structured Syllabus. </p>
                                <br />
                                <p>The International General Certificate syllabus consists of two units: focusing on Hazard Effect and management (Unit IGC1) and controlling workplace hazards (Unit GC2). Assessment is by two written examinations and a workplace-based practical assignment (Unit GC3).</p>
                                <br />
                                <p><b>UNIT IGC 1: Management of International Health & Safety</b></p>
                                <br />
                                <p>•	Foundations in health and safety</p>
                                <p>•	Health and safety management systems 1 - Plan</p>   
                                <p>•	Health and safety management systems 2 - Do</p>  
                                <p>•	Health and safety management systems 3 - Check</p>  
                                <p>•	Health and safety management systems 4 - Act</p>  
                                 
                                 
                                 <br />
                                <p><b>UNIT IGC 2: Control of International Workplace Risks</b></p>
                                <br />
                                <p>•	Workplace hazards and risk control</p>
                                <p>•	Transport hazards and risk control</p>   
                                <p>•	Musculoskeletal hazards and risk control</p>  
                                <p>•	Work equipment hazards and risk control</p>  
                                <p>•	Electrical safety</p>
                                <p>•	Fire safety</p>
                                <p>•	Chemical and biological health hazards and risk control</p>
                                <p>•	Physical and psychological health hazards and risk control</p>  

                                <br />
                                <p><b>UNIT IGC3: International Health & Safety Practical Application</b></p>
