                                <h3>Why Nebosh International General Certificate???</h3>
                                <br />
                                <p>Now a day’s companies and industries are looking HSE Professionals to meet their demands of occupational health and safety. They offer different designations in their companies such as </p>
                                <br />
                                    <p style="padding-left:25px;">	• Jr. Safety/HSE Officer.</p>
                                    <p style="padding-left:25px;">	• Safety/HSE Officer.</p>
                                    <p style="padding-left:25px;">	• Safety/HSE Trainer.</p>
                                    <p style="padding-left:25px;">  • Sr. Safety/ HSE Officer</p>
                                    <p style="padding-left:25px;">	• Sr. Safety/HSE Trainer.</p>
                                    <p style="padding-left:25px;">	• Safety/HSE Engineers, </p>
                                    <p style="padding-left:25px;">	• Sr. Safety/HSE Engineer.</p>
                                    <p style="padding-left:25px;">  • Asst. Safety/HSE Manager.</p>
                                    <p style="padding-left:25px;">	• Safety/HSE Manager.</p>
                                   
                                <br />
                                <p>NEBOSH IGC programme is the most preferred certificate for gaining a safety jobs in different fields such as   oil and gas, power plant, construction industries in different countries in GULF region as well as you may get job offers in Foreign Countries.  </p>
                                <br />
                                <p>Once you successfully completion of the NEBOSH IGC programme you will enable you to join for NEBOSH INTERNATIONAL DIPLOMA programme.</p>
                                <br />
                                <p>On successful completion of the qualification, the Diploma holder may apply for Graduate member (Grad IOSH) of the Institution of Occupational Safety and Health (IOSH), the major UK professional body in the field (www.iosh.co.uk). This is the first step to becoming a Chartered Safety and Health Practitioner as a Chartered Member of IOSH (CMIOSH). And also associate membership (AIIRSM) of the International Institute of Risk and Safety Management (IIRSM).</p>
                                
                                
                                <hr />
                                <h3>Who can take Nebosh International General Certificate???</h3>
                                <br />
                                <p>The NEBOSH National / International General Certificate in Occupational Safety & Health is designed for personnel with health & safety responsibilities, e.g. managers, supervisors, safety officers, non-safety specialists etc & who need a grounding & recognized qualification in occupational safety & health.</p>
                                <br />
                                <p>It is also beneficial for those wanting to further their career in the HSE field or those who wish to enhance their HSE knowledge.</p>
                                
                                
